==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hysteresis
<hw>Hys`te*re"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/ to be behind, to lag.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>A lagging
or retardation of the effect, when the forces acting upon a body are
changed, as if from velocity or internal friction; a temporary
resistance to change from a condition previously induced, observed in
magnetism, thermoelectricity, etc., on reversal of polarity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hysteretic</ent>⟦br⟧
